arxiv.org/abs/2202.03753\">Semantic features of object concepts generated with GPT-3</a> - 2022. [<a href=\"https://scholar.google.com/scholar?cluster=16958563995984242923&#x26;hl=en&#x26;as_sdt=0,5\">All Versions</a>]. Testing the semantic attributes of the concepts generated by the large language model GPT-3.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-08-27T07:55:21.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"YuzheSHI/awesome-agi-cocosci","categoryHTML":"<h2>Papers</h2><h4>Theory of Concepts</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/concepts/\">Concepts</a> - <em><strong>Plato Stanford</strong></em>. A collection of the computational philosophical debates about the concepts.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-08-27T07:25:20.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"YuzheSHI/awesome-agi-cocosci","categoryHTML":"<h2>Papers</h2><h4>Theory of Concepts</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Theory-theory\">Theory-theory</a> - <em><strong>Wikipedia</strong></em>. Wikipedia for the Theory theory, a perspective that contextualizes concepts in theoretical (or empirical) systems.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-08-27T07:25:20.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"YuzheSHI/awesome-agi-cocosci","categoryHTML":"<h2>Papers</h2><h4>Association Test</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://faculty.washington.edu/agg/pdf/Nosek%20&#x26;%20al.IATatage7.2007.pdf\">The Implicit Association Test at Age 7: A Methodological and Conceptual Review</a> - <em><strong>Social psychology and the unconscious: The automaticity of higher mental processes (pp. 265–292), Psychology Press</strong></em>, 2007. [<a href=\"https://scholar.google.com/scholar?cluster=16189750920013376566&#x26;hl=en&#x26;as_sdt=0,5\">All Versions</a>]. The 7th year review for the IAT.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-08-27T04:25:27.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"YuzheSHI/awesome-agi-cocosci","categoryHTML":"<h2>Papers</h2><h4>Association Test</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://faculty.washington.edu/agg/pdf/Gwald_Nosek_ZEITSCHR_2001.OCR.pdf\">Health of the Implicit Association Test at age 3</a> - <em><strong>Zeitschrift für Experimentelle Psychologie</strong></em>, 2001. [<a href=\"https://scholar.google.com/scholar?cluster=10868478693422595588&#x26;hl=en&#x26;as_sdt=0,5\">All Versions</a>]. The 3rd year review for the IAT.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-08-27T04:22:39.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"YuzheSHI/awesome-agi-cocosci","categoryHTML":"<h2>Papers</h2><h4>Association Test</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://faculty.fortlewis.edu/burke_b/Senior/BLINK%20replication/IAT.pdf\">Measuring Individual Differences in Implicit Cognition: The Implicit Association Test</a> - <em><strong>Journal of Personality and Social Psychology</strong></em>, 1998. [<a href=\"https://scholar.google.com/scholar?cluster=302378224541015580&#x26;hl=en&#x26;as_sdt=0,5\">All Versions</a>]. The original paper introducing the Implicit Association Test.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-08-27T03:26:08.000Z"}]}},"pageContext":{"type":"day","from":1661558400000,"to":1661644799999,"previousId":"2022-08-28","nextId":"2022-08-26","nextName":"Aug 26th, 2022","previousName":"Aug 28th, 2022"}},"staticQueryHashes":["228695001","2744905544","2828988102"]}